# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
Intuition is very simple, we just need to take number started with left range and do the AND operation with consecutive numbers untill the number reaches its value equal to right range value.
# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
Need to avoid some of the cases.
1. If any one of the left or right range value is zero then we return 0 since Anynum&0 = 0.
2. If binary representation of left and right numbers are of different digits then also we should result 0.
Example: suppose we have got left as 1 and right as 64. So the binary values are left = 1, right = 1000000.
So if we start with left AND with left + 1, i.e. 1 & 2 result becomes 0. So from next operation onwards it is always zero.

Once we validate these..then the solution is simple. Take the value and performe AND operation with next number.

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    int rangeBitwiseAnd(int left, int right) {
        // if both the numbers left and right is same, return anyone
        if(left==0 || right ==0) return 0;

        // if there binary numbers for left and right are of different digits
        if((int)log2(left)!=(int)log2(right)) return 0; 
        //initialize output with left range
        int res = left;

        while(left<right){
            res &= ++left;
        }
        return res;
    }
};
