Easy python- find LSB and keep flipping as long as we're within the range. 
This all hinges on the fact that the 2's complement of n is -n. So the loop runs until we exceed the range from m-n (inclusive) and we keep getting the least significant bit and subtracting that from n. When we're no longer within the range, we return the value of n we've arrived at. 

```
class Solution:
    def rangeBitwiseAnd(self, m: int, n: int) -> int:
        if m==n:
            return m

        while (m<n):
            n -= (n & -n)

        return n
```

