solutions.content:
If a bit at ```i```-th (```0 <= i <= 31```) position is ```0``` in either ```left``` or ```right``` then the bit in the result at this position will also be ```0```, since we need at least one ```0``` to set all bits to ```0```. If not, i.e., both have their bits set at this ```i```, then check if the gap between these two numbers is less than or equal to ```2^i - 1```. On observation, one can see that the max-run of ```1```s (or ```0```s) is equal to ```2^i``` for the ```i```-th bit. Thus, if gap between inputs is greater than this range, then this range has at least one ```0``` for this ```i```.
```
class Solution {
public:
    int rangeBitwiseAnd(int l, int r)
    {
        if (l == r) return l;
        if (!l || !r) return 0;
        int n = 0;
        for (int i = 0; i < 31; ++i) {
            if (((l & (1 << i)) == 0) || ((r & (1 << i)) == 0)) continue;
            if ((r - l <= (1 << i) - 1)) {
                n |= (1 << i);
            }
        }
        return n;
    }
};
```

