Hello Leetcoders, hope you are well.

Let's proceed to this valid palindrome II problem.

**What Problem statement is saying**
```
You have a String s, return true if it is palindrome else false.
Operation : you can delete one character from the String to make it palindrome
```

Now I think you know what is a palindrome String 
An string which you can read same from left to right & right to left

e.g : racecar

**Base code for palindrome**
```

// T(n) - O(n) 
// S(n) - O(n)


public boolean isPalindrome(String s) {
	int left = 0, right = s.length() - 1;

	while(left < right) {
		if(s.charAt(left) != s.charAt(right)) return false;

		left++;
		right--;
	}

	return true;
}	
```

Now if you think problem said that we can delete one character from the string(if needed) to make this string palindrome

**how can we do that?**

let me explain it to you by using one example 

e.g acdda

here you can see first and last character is same so we skip to the next iteration. Now at 2nd place we have **c** from start and **d** from end. here mis-matched the characters. what we can do here? a simple deletion of the character.

The question is which one we have to delete, The start one or end one. what we can do is delete start and check is it palindrome and delete end and check is it palindrome. do OR operation to get the desired output

How you can delete? just call another fuunction by skiping the desired index of the character 

in our exmaple we call another function which return boolean value
retrun callFunction("dd") || callFunction("cd");

callFunction("dd") -> skipped start position i.e **'c'**
callFunction("cd") -> Skipped last position i.e. **'d'**


Code 
```
public boolean validPalindrome(String s) {
        int left = 0;
        int right = s.length() - 1;

        while(left < right) {
            if(s.charAt(left) != s.charAt(right)) {
