the logic is, there will be at most one mismatch of characters, so you have to check ignoring that one character, the rest of the string is a palindrome or not.
now we all know that, aPa is a palindrome if P is another string which itself is a palindrome.
now you might be given that abPa or aPba. 
so you just need to check ignoring the b, the rest is a palindrome or not.
if you're given abPa, you have already checked the outer parts, now see if P is a palindrom or not, if yes then you can ignore b and make it a full palindrome.

if P is not a palindrome, it means there may need to perform some deletion inside P as well, which will make the total deletion more than 1 because we have already kept a character to delete.

The same thing also applies for aPba.
