Here, canDelete is used to determine if one deletion is done or not. Initially it is true, which means we can still delete one character, after that if we delete one character, it would be false for next calls. 
Recursive will be only used if case if left and right characters dont match. 

```
class Solution {
    public boolean validPalindrome(String s) {
        return validPalindromeUtil(s,0,s.length()-1,true);
    }

    boolean validPalindromeUtil(String s,int l,int r,boolean canDelete){

        while(l < r) {
        if(s.charAt(l) == s.charAt(r)){
            l++;r--;
        }
        else if(canDelete){
            return validPalindromeUtil(s,l+1,r,false) || validPalindromeUtil(s,l,r-1,false);
        }
        else
            return false;
     }
        return true;
    }
}
