**Idea:**
* Use 2 pointers, 1 at the beginning of s and 1 at the end
* Move them inwards as long as they point to same chars and don't cross each other
* If the pointers aren't same then check if:
	* s[i, j) is a palindrome. If yes, then s[j] can be deleted to get a palindrome
	* s[i+1, j+1) is a palindrome. If yes, then s[i] can be deleted to get a palindrome 
>**T/S:** O(n)/O(1), where n = size(s)  
