**Please Upvote If It Helps**

**Algorithm**
* Initialize the pointers for **left and right** also initialize the count val for counting **left deleted and right deelted chars**

* Count the **left deleted chars** using a **while loop** untill our **left count value not exceed 1** or **string does not finish**
* Count the **right deleted chars** using a **while loop** untill our **left count value not exceed 1** or **string does not finish**
* then check cnt values 
* **if cnt==0 or cnt == 1 return true (atmost one)**
* **if cnt>1 return false                      (freater then one)**

```
class Solution {
public:
    bool validPalindrome(string s) 
    {
        // initializing the pointers
        int l = 0;
        int r = s.size()-1;

        // initializing the left right deleted cnt chars
        int cnt_l = 0;
        int cnt_r = 0;

        // for left deleted elements
        while(l<=r)
        {
            if(s[l]==s[r])
            {
                l++;
                r--;
            }
            else
            {
                cnt_l++;
                l++;
            }

            if(cnt_l>1)
                break;
        }

        // reinitializing the pointer for counting the right deleted chars
        l = 0;
        r = s.size()-1;

        // for right
        while(l<=r)
        {
            if(s[l]==s[r])
            {
                l++;
                r--;
            }
            else
            {
                cnt_r++;
                r--;
            }

            if(cnt_r>1)
                break;
        }

        // palindrom condition
        if(cnt_l==0 or cnt_r==0)
            return true;

        // atmost one char deleted condition
        if(cnt_l==1 or cnt_r==1)
            return true;

        return false;
    }
};
```

