-> i--> intial pointer , j--> final pointer
-> travese it from end , start both side (i++ , j-- );
-> if s[i] == s[j] --> satisfy palindrom condition okk go forward
->but if s[i] != s[j] so we can do two thing
either remove from left side ( i side deletion ) or righr side (j side deletion)

(find useful upvote it vro :) )
-> i am choosing left first and right next and use counter( countI and countJ) to know whether i have chance to remove from left /right side or not

**note i am not deleting from both side in my deletion condition box there is condition like that only one char is delete

--> i use storeI and storeJ to for the remember point that where first inequality come and i was used my deletion power ( delete one character)
because in testcase like :-
if first inequality is come in string i go with 'i' side deletion and it satisfy upto some length but not make my string completly palindromic because 'j' side deletion make complete palindromic to my string so , at that i cann't do 'j' side deletion on present index
(it delete two character) i use that index where my first inequality ( or on which i use my i side is required to do it ** we only delete one character max**)

so if both possibility fail mean (we check from i ,j side deletion )
return false otherwise true

